  "texts": [
    "Since both embeddings and KV pairs are generated simultaneously by the encoder, they offer similar improvements in LLM efficiency, including higher inference speed and reduced computational costs.",
    "Modality integration.",
    "Compressed texts can be considered a new modality, similar to vision and speech.",
    "In vision-language models, for example, an image encoder converts an image into a list of embeddings, which are then used by an LLM decoder for downstream tasks such as image captioning or QA (Zhang et al., 2024a).",
    "This architecture parallels that of prompt compression models, where an encoder compresses natural language into special embeddings and an LLM decoder utilizes these continuous vectors."
  ],
